M||tx|---
M||titl|Put Interaction Logic in Event Handlers
M||impa|md
M||impa|avoids effect re-runs and duplicate side effects
M||tags|rerender, useEffect, events, side-effects, dependencies
M||tx|---
M|Put |tx|If a side effect is triggered by a specific us action (submit, click, drag), run it in that event handler. Do not md the action as state + effect; it makes effects re-run on unrelated changes and can duplicate the action.
M|Put |**In|**
M|Put |tx|```tsx
M|Put |tx|fn Form() {
M|Put |tx|const [submitted, setSubmitted] = useState(false)
M|Put |tx|const theme = useContext(ThemeContext)
M|Put |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Put |tx|if (submitted) {
M|Put |tx|post('/ap/register')
M|Put |tx|showToast('Registered', theme)
M|Put |tx|}
M|Put |tx|}, [submitted, theme])
M|Put |tx|return <button onClick={() => setSubmitted(true)}>Submit</button>
M|Put |tx|}
M|Put |tx|```
M|Put |**Co|**
M|Put |tx|```tsx
M|Put |tx|fn Form() {
M|Put |tx|const theme = useContext(ThemeContext)
M|Put |tx|fn handleSubmit() {
M|Put |tx|post('/ap/register')
M|Put |tx|showToast('Registered', theme)
M|Put |tx|}
M|Put |tx|return <button onClick={handleSubmit}>Submit</button>
M|Put |tx|}
M|Put |tx|```
M|Put |Refe|[shd this code move to an event handler?](https://rc.dv/learn/removing-effect-dependencies#shd-this-code-move-to-an-event-handler)